    <div align="left" id="post_message_389482">Nymm was in early beta, and played through the end of beta. You're awfully critical of a set of mechanics that you obviously never played. The early combat system (though it admittedly DID need polish), was actually quite fun. It had lots of potential, but was scrapped for the typical combat seen in every other RPG.<br />
 <br />
My favorite Vanguard was beta 2.5 when combat, death, and travel actually meant something. Community was a must (i.e. grouping for level and quest progression) and coaxed people into banding together to do things rather than the soloers paradise offered now.</div>
